---
import LegalLayout from "@layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import { BRAND } from "~/lib/brand";
---

<LegalLayout
  seo={{
    title: "Terms of Service",
    description:
      "Terms governing use of northvaleroofing.com. Service contracts are separate signed documents.",
    pathname: "/legal/terms",
  }}
  title="Terms of Service"
  effectiveDate="2026-04-22"
>
  <p>
    These terms govern your use of {BRAND.domain} (the "Site"). A contract for roofing services is a separate
    signed document between you and {BRAND.legalName}. Nothing on this Site is itself a service
    contract.
  </p>
  <h2>Site content</h2>
  <p>
    Pricing ranges, timelines, and material descriptions are informational and subject to change.
    The only binding numbers are the ones on your signed estimate.
  </p>
  <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    All content, design, and logos are © {BRAND.legalName}. You may share links or short quotes with
    attribution; republication requires written permission.
  </p>
  <h2>No warranty of Site content</h2>
  <p>
    Site content is provided "as is." We don't warrant that it's error-free or complete. Rely on the
    written estimate and contract for binding commitments.
  </p>
  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent allowed by law, {BRAND.legalName}'s liability arising from Site use is
    limited to the greater of $100 or the amount you paid us in the twelve months before the event
    giving rise to the claim. Services-contract liability is governed by the signed contract itself.
  </p>
  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>Texas. Any dispute arising from Site use is venued in Montgomery or Harris County, Texas.</p>
  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>{BRAND.email}</p>
</LegalLayout>
